+descr-method('diff', 'diff', 'obs.diff([fn], [seed])').
  On each value from original observable calls #[b fn]
  function with previous and current value as arguments.
  At first time calls #[b fn] with #[b seed] and current value.
  Emits whatever #[b fn] returns.

p.
  If no #[b seed] provided the first value will be used as a seed,
  and result observable won't emit on first value.

p.
  If no #[b fn] function provided, #[tt function(a, b) {return [a, b]}] will be used.
  If you want to omit #[b fn] but provide #[b seed], pass #[tt null] as #[b fn].

